	p#q1aDescribe So what is stuckness?  There are two kinds:  You’re stuck, or the work is.  You’re stuck whenever you’re doing something you don’t want to.  If you’re eating chocolate chip cookies and really wish you weren’t, if you’re grazing over articles or pintrest or doing the dishes when you want to be writing, you’re scrambling frantically to make a deadline, again.  You’re stuck in traffic, you’re stuck in a shitty marriage. You know the feeling. If not, try the construction this way:  you’re stuck whenever you’re not doing something you want to do.  You’re not writing scene three, you’re not starting the new book, you’re not doing enough self-promotion.  
