	#start5.nextLink(onclick="start6()", style="display:block") I need more help
	p.subDescribe If you’re facing more than one army, pick one.  It can be the once you feel you have the best chance of beating, or the most formidable one.  Either way, it’s bigger and stronger than you, so force won’t work.   You can’t beat them into submission, will your way over them, or shame them into silence.  
	p.subDescribe When you have to negotiate, and you do because remember, they’re winning, the first step, hard as it is, is empathy.  Yes, they’re the competition, but you won’t be able to spot a compromise from an adversarial point of view. Be compassionate.  
